# NextAuth v5 Credentials Auth

## Proxy (Next.js 16 convention)

The auth guard is `src/proxy.ts` — Next.js 16 uses `proxy` instead of `middleware`:

```ts
export { auth as proxy } from "@/auth";
export const config = {
  matcher: ["/((?!_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico|icon.svg).*)"],
};
```

**Never rename this back to `middleware.ts`** — it causes a deprecation error in Next.js 16.

## Public paths

Declared in the `authorized` callback in `src/auth.ts`:

```ts
const PUBLIC = ["/login", "/register", "/api/auth", "/api/register", "/api/setup"];
if (PUBLIC.some(p => request.nextUrl.pathname.startsWith(p))) return true;
```

To add a new public path (e.g. a webhook), add it to this array only — do NOT add it to
`src/proxy.ts`.

## Session in Server Components

```ts
import { auth } from "@/auth";

export default async function MyPage() {
  const session = await auth();
  if (!session) redirect("/login");
  const userId = (session.user as { id: string }).id;
  // ...
}
```

## Session in Client Components

```tsx
"use client";
import { useSession } from "next-auth/react";

export function MyComponent() {
  const { data: session, status } = useSession();
  if (status === "loading") return null;
  if (!session) return <p>Not logged in</p>;
  return <p>Hello {session.user?.name}</p>;
}
```

`SessionProvider` is already in `src/app/layout.tsx` — do not add it again.

## Sign-in (client)

```tsx
import { signIn } from "next-auth/react";

const result = await signIn("credentials", {
  email, password,
  redirect: false,   // always false — handle redirect manually
});
if (result?.error) { /* show error */ }
else router.push(from ?? "/");
```

## Sign-out (client)

```tsx
import { signOut } from "next-auth/react";
signOut({ callbackUrl: "/login" });
```

## JWT shape

The JWT contains `token.id` (set in the `jwt` callback). Access via:

```ts
session.user.id  // after casting: (session.user as { id: string }).id
```

## Env vars

| Var | Notes |
|-----|-------|
| `NEXTAUTH_SECRET` | Required. `openssl rand -base64 32` to generate. |
| `AUTH_SECRET` | Same value — NextAuth v5 reads both. |
| `NEXTAUTH_URL` | Only for local dev (`http://localhost:7854`). **Do not set on Vercel.** |

## Password hashing

All passwords hashed with `bcrypt.hash(password, 12)` (rounds = 12).
Verify with `bcrypt.compare(plain, hash)`. Import from `bcryptjs` (not `bcrypt`).
